headlines.description: — All-Star Darius Garland scored 18 of his 30 points in the fourth quarter and the NBA-leading Cleveland Cavaliers rallied for a 109-104 victory over the Brooklyn Nets on Tuesday night, matching the longest winning streak in franchise history at 15...
headlines.shortLinkText: NBA-leading Cavaliers beat Nets 109-104 for their second 15-game win streak of season

headlines.description: — Cade Cunningham had 27 points and 10 assists, and the Detroit Pistons beat NBA-worst Washington 123-103 on Tuesday night in a physical game that included two late flagrant fouls by the Wizards.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cade Cunningham leads Pistons past NBA-worst Wizards 123-103 in physical game

headlines.description: — Tyrese Haliburton described it as “a football play” — and he converted the extra point, too.
headlines.shortLinkText: Pacers' Tyrese Haliburton converts last-second 'football play' into 4 points to stun Bucks

events.name: LA Clippers at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Zion Williamson had 22 points, 12 assists and 10 rebounds, and the New Orleans Pelicans snapped a four-game slide with a 127-120 victory over the Los Angeles Clippers on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Zion Williamson has triple-double to lead Pelicans past Clippers 127-120
